        "published": "2025-12-01T23:15:53.227",
        "lastModified": "2026-02-06T16:34:33.003",
        "vulnStatus": "Analyzed",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "MCP Watch is a comprehensive security scanner for Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers. In 0.1.2 and earlier, the MCPScanner class contains a critical Command Injection vulnerability in the cloneRepo method. The application passes the user-supplied githubUrl argument directly to a system shell via execSync without sanitization. This allows an attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the host machine by appending shell metacharacters to the URL."
          }
        ],
